"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-sport-othersport-1934680-usa-basketball-olympics-noah-lyles\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  Team USA's basketball squad clinchedthe Olympic gold medal in Paris, triumphing over France with a score of 98-87 in a nail-biting final.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 139, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2, \"end\": 10, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999850151654, \"rank\": 8.830218259554007e-09, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 64, \"end\": 69, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999995663984, \"rank\": 4.3351481246362915e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 87, \"end\": 93, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8159136935154139, \"rank\": 0.2256164437598545, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The American team, demonstrating their dominance, secured their fifth consecutive gold on Saturday.\", \"from\": 140, \"to\": 239, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 144, \"end\": 152, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.99956831976446, \"rank\": 0.00043084686631436446, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite the electric support for the home team, Team USA maintained composure and a five-point lead by the close of the first quarter.\", \"from\": 241, \"to\": 375, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 289, \"end\": 297, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999850151654, \"rank\": 8.830218259554007e-09, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They momentarily lost ground in the third quarter but swiftly regained a five-point lead in the fourth, dashing any hopes of a French comeback.\", \"from\": 376, \"to\": 519, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 503, \"end\": 509, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9873612271375112, \"rank\": 0.008737579234285985, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a cheeky response to America's 100-meter sprint champion Noah Lyles, who previously criticised NBA teams for dubbing themselves 'World Champions', USA Basketball's social media celebrated the win with a hint of sarcasm.\", \"from\": 521, \"to\": 743, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 581, \"end\": 591, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 619, \"end\": 622, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 0.9996507608802515, \"rank\": 0.00034915365781620303, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 671, \"end\": 685, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9904190122872338, \"rank\": 0.00967367103618734, \"text\": \"USA Basketball\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles had expressed his frustration, saying, \\\"You know the thing that hurts me the most is that I have to watch the NBA Finals and they have 'world champion' on their head,\\\" adding, \\\"World champion of what?\", \"from\": 745, \"to\": 951, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 861, \"end\": 871, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Finals\", \"score\": 0.9999182815280793, \"rank\": 4.0819607940209e-05, \"text\": \"NBA Finals\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Finals\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Finals\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The United States?\", \"from\": 952, \"to\": 970, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 956, \"end\": 969, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999986596976556, \"rank\": 3.6793590062210796e-07, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Do not get me wrong, I love the U.S., at times, but that ain't the world.\\\"\", \"from\": 971, \"to\": 1045, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles' remarks did not sit well with basketball enthusiasts, and despite his Olympic glory, he found himself at odds with some patriotic fans, with a few even confessing to rooting against him during the track events in Paris.\", \"from\": 1047, \"to\": 1273, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1267, \"end\": 1272, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999995663984, \"rank\": 4.3351481246362915e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The US basketball team's official social media page celebrated their Olympic victory with a post that read: \\\"Are we the World Champs now? \\\"\", \"from\": 1275, \"to\": 1414, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1279, \"end\": 1297, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.755150872996214e-13, \"text\": \"US basketball team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This comment seemed to have been etched in the minds of the players.\", \"from\": 1415, \"to\": 1483, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, fans outside of the US were quick to point out that while the American team can call themselves Olympic champions, the current world champions are Germany.\", \"from\": 1487, \"to\": 1651, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1516, \"end\": 1518, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999440651679, \"rank\": 5.592541325523217e-08, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1558, \"end\": 1566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.99956831976446, \"rank\": 0.00043084686631436446, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1643, \"end\": 1650, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9989418646502003, \"rank\": 0.0010592224462415056, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They clinched the 2023 FIBA Basketball World Cup for the first time in their history by defeating Serbia in the final.\", \"from\": 1652, \"to\": 1770, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1750, \"end\": 1756, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9922182350638717, \"rank\": 0.007840848525376068, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The US team finished fourth after losing the third-place match to Canada.\", \"from\": 1772, \"to\": 1845, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1776, \"end\": 1778, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999440651679, \"rank\": 5.592541325523217e-08, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1838, \"end\": 1844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9536477540065218, \"rank\": 0.04217705011168076, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After his 100m victory,Lyles also bagged a bronze medal in the 200m.\", \"from\": 1849, \"to\": 1917, \"entities\": [{